SIMPLE: pseudomorph
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pseudomorph
<hw>Pseu"do*morph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Pseudomorphous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An irregular or
deceptive form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>A <cref>pseudomorphous
crystal</cref>, such as a crystal consisting of quartz, but having the
cubic form of fluor spar, the fluor crystal having been changed to
quartz by a process of substitution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudomorphism</ent>⟦br⟧
